Each thread stores and prints its own value.

🔹 Important Methods
Method	Meaning
set(value)	Set value for current thread
get()	Get value for current thread
remove()	Remove value (very important to avoid memory leaks)
🔹 Where ThreadLocal is Used in Real Applications?

Since you're learning Spring Boot and backend development 👨‍💻, this is important:

1️⃣ In Spring Security

To store logged-in user information per request.

2️⃣ In Hibernate

To store session per thread.

3️⃣ In Logging (MDC)

To store requestId for tracking logs.

🔹 ThreadLocal vs Normal Variable
Normal Variable	ThreadLocal
Shared between threads	Separate copy per thread
Needs synchronization	No synchronization needed
Can cause race condition	No race condition
🔹 Important Warning ⚠

If you're using ThreadPool (like in Spring Boot web apps):

👉 Always call remove() after work is done.

Why?
Because threads are reused in thread pools → old data may leak to next request.

Example:

try {
    threadLocal.set("User1");
    // business logic
} finally {
    threadLocal.remove();
}
